-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526068\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526068\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bir1665702706773.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bir1665702706773.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bir1665702706773.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bir1665702706773\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Data Integrity on PostgreSQL\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> commands are supported.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bir1665702706773__section_w3671ab1b5b1_w3672ab1b5_w3673ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bir1665702706773__section_w3674ab1b5b3_w3675ab1b5_w3676ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d462775e62\">\n                       \n Transaction Control\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bir1665702706773__p_d57947e1_d57948e1_d57949e1\">The connector does not change transaction state before entering and before leaving the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> ProcScript statement. This is left to the ODBC driver manager. If possible, avoid transaction processing because the connector cannot manage a transaction that it did not initiate.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bir1665702706773__p_d57950e1_d57951e1_d57952e1\">The commands that involve transaction management are:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bir1665702706773__li_d26273e1_d26274e1_d26275e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> (Uniface command)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bir1665702706773__li_d26276e1_d26277e1_d26278e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> (Uniface command)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bir1665702706773__li_d26279e1_d26280e1_d26281e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">commit transaction</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bir1665702706773__li_d26282e1_d26283e1_d26284e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">rollback transaction</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bir1665702706773__li_d26285e1_d26286e1_d26287e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">begin transaction</code>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"bir1665702706773__note_w3683ab1b5b3b9_w3684ab1b5b3_w3685ab1b5_w3686ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> If you perform transaction management, once the transaction finishes you must ensure that the logon path is returned to the same state that it was in before the transaction management was performed. If do not do this, the PostgreSQL driver transaction manager does not understand the correct state of the connection.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bir1665702706773__section_w3677ab1b5b5_w3678ab1b5_w3679ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d462775e113\">\n                       \n Locking Strategies\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bir1665702706773__p_d57956e1_d57957e1_d57958e1\">The connector supports Optimistic, Cautious and Paranoid locking. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qvp1665702561079.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qvp1665702561079.html\" title=\"Locking means protecting one or more rows from being overwritten by other users while you are working with those rows. Working with rows can be defined as either the simple act of reading those rows from the database, or the act of modifying those rows after retrieving them and before storing, or the act of storing those modified rows. The state that initiates locking depends on the type of locking which has been applied or defined.\">Locking Strategies</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bir1665702706773__section_w3680ab1b5b7_w3681ab1b5_w3682ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d462775e129\">\n                       \n Referential Integrity\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bir1665702706773__p_d57962e1_d57963e1_d57964e1\">The PGS connector supports the creation of scripts that will enforce the referential integrity in the database.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lnt1665702561005.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Transaction Control</a><p>A transaction is a complete, logical unit of work. It usually involves adding, deleting or updating one or more logically related records in one or more databases. With Uniface, you can explicitly define a transaction with the commit ProcScript instruction. If an error occurs, a transaction can be rolled back with the rollback ProcScript instruction.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qvp1665702561079.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Locking Strategies</a><p>Locking means protecting one or more rows from being overwritten by other users while you are working with those rows. Working with rows can be defined as either the simple act of reading those rows from the database, or the act of modifying those rows after retrieving them and before storing, or the act of storing those modified rows. The state that initiates locking depends on the type of locking which has been applied or defined.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fnf1665702703926.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Referential Integrity</a><p>Referential integrity is a standard feature of relational database design that prevents users or applications from entering inconsistent data. Most relational databases have referential integrity rules that you can apply when you create a relationship between tables.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526068\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526068\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Data Integrity on PostgreSQL Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Data Integrity on PostgreSQL The commit and rollback commands are supported. Transaction Control The connector does not change transaction state before entering and before leaving the sql ProcScript statement. This is left to the ODBC driver manager. If possible, avoid transaction processing because the connector cannot manage a transaction that it did not initiate. The commands that involve transaction management are: commit (Uniface command) rollback (Uniface command) commit transaction rollback transaction begin transaction Note: If you perform transaction management, once the transaction finishes you must ensure that the logon path is returned to the same state that it was in before the transaction management was performed. If do not do this, the PostgreSQL driver transaction manager does not understand the correct state of the connection. Locking Strategies The connector supports Optimistic, Cautious and Paranoid locking. For more information, see Locking Strategies . Referential Integrity The PGS connector supports the creation of scripts that will enforce the referential integrity in the database. Related Links Transaction Control A transaction is a complete, logical unit of work. It usually involves adding, deleting or updating one or more logically related records in one or more databases. With Uniface, you can explicitly define a transaction with the commit ProcScript instruction. If an error occurs, a transaction can be rolled back with the rollback ProcScript instruction. Locking Strategies Locking means protecting one or more rows from being overwritten by other users while you are working with those rows. Working with rows can be defined as either the simple act of reading those rows from the database, or the act of modifying those rows after retrieving them and before storing, or the act of storing those modified rows. The state that initiates locking depends on the type of locking which has been applied or defined. Referential Integrity Referential integrity is a standard feature of relational database design that prevents users or applications from entering inconsistent data. Most relational databases have referential integrity rules that you can apply when you create a relationship between tables. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}